ions are counted false.\r\n- Current tuned algorithm has around 100% recall on the default 10-link fold and ~3.45% apparent precision.\r\n- We need a curated, traceable precision benchmark that labels ordinary suggestions.\r\n\r\nRequired outcome:\r\n1. Inspect the current benchmark, CLI, evidence, report, and research artifacts.\r\n2. Run the current suggestion pipeline against Space Rocks and create a deterministic stratified sample of at least 150 suggestions. Stratify across score/rank buckets, evidence types, document areas/subsystems, and include top-1/top-3/top-5 suggestions per document where possible. Avoid duplicate document-target pairs.\r\n3. Curate each sampled suggestion into one of exactly:\r\n   - valid_missing_link\r\n   - plausible_but_unnecessary\r\n   - incorrect\r\n   Include concise, evidence-based rationale and enough source metadata to audit the label. Inspect the referenced document and target code, not just filenames. Do not silently infer labels from existing codemap inclusion alone.\r\n4. Store the benchmark as a deterministic, reviewable JSON artifact under research/codemap-precision/ and add a concise methodology/report Markdown file there.\r\n5. Add or extend Go tooling so the labeled benchmark can be evaluated reproducibly. Report at minimum:\r\n   - overall precision where only valid_missing_link counts correct\r\n   - acceptance precision where valid_missing_link + plausible_but_unnecessary count non-junk\r\n   - precision@1, precision@3, precision@5 per document\r\n   - breakdown by evidence kind and score/rank bucket\r\n   - label counts and sampling coverage\r\n6. Add focused tests for parsing, deterministic sampling/evaluation, and metric calculations.\r\n7. Run gofmt and go test ./... . Run the real evaluation against the created benchmark and include the resulting metrics in the Markdown report.\r\n8. Commit all finished work on the current branch with a focused commit message. Do not push.\r\n\r\nConstraints:\r\n- Preserve the existing 51-link recall benchmark.\r\n- Do not modify Space Rocks.\r\n- Do not loosen the suggestion algorithm just to improve the benchmark.\r\n- Do not fabricate source inspection. Every label needs an auditable rationale grounded in the document and code target.\r\n- Keep generated scratch output out of the commit.\r\n- If the repo is dirty at start, preserve unrelated work and do not overwrite it; report any conflict.\r\n- Use the existing project conventions and avoid broad unrelated cleanup.\r\n\r\nAt the end, report: changed files, commit hash, test results, benchmark size and label distribution, overall precision, acceptance precision, precision@1/@3/@5, and any limitations.\r\nresult= Implemented and committed as `2420dea` (`Add curated codemap precision benchmark`).\r\n\r\nChanged:\r\n\r\n- Precision evaluator CLI and Go package\r\n- Deterministic stratified sampler\r\n- Focused parser, sampling, and metric tests\r\n- 150-row auditable benchmark artifact\r\n- Methodology/results report\r\n\r\nBenchmark:\r\n\r\n- Size: 150 suggestions across 10 documents\r\n- Labels: 98 valid, 26 plausible, 26 incorrect\r\n- Overall precision: 65.33%\r\n- Acceptance precision: 82.67%\r\n- Precision@1/@3/@5: 80.00% / 73.33% / 74.00%\r\n\r\nPer-document @1/@3/@5: data sync `0/0/0%`; observability `100/66.67/80%`; devtools client/server `100/100/100%`; player-data HTTP `100/100/80%`; realtime `100/100/100%`; websocket lifecycle `100/100/100%`; diagnostic aggregator `0/0/0%`; respawn `100/66.67/80%`; profile stats `100/100/100%`.\r\n\r\n`go test ./...` passed before commit. The original 10-link recall fold remains 100% recall. After commit, unrelated untracked concurrent files appeared and currently cause a separate `codemapbench` test compile failure; they were preserved and excluded from the commit.\r\n--- 019f7aac-3d68-7493-9580-c39af99cfcbb.jsonl ---\r\nContinue the partially implemented codemap precision benchmark in this repo. Existing untracked files internal/codemapprecision/model.go and precision.go were left by a previous logged Codex run. Work only on the tooling stage now so this call finishes promptly.\r\n\r\nTasks:\r\n1. Inspect the existing codemap benchmark/report/CLI structures and the partial codemapprecision package.\r\n2. Correct, complete, and gofmt the package. Add focused tests for benchmark loading/validation, deterministic candidate ranking and stratified sampling, metric calculations including overall precision, acceptance precision, precision@1/@3/@5, and evidence/score/rank breakdowns.\r\n3. Add a small command or research utility under cmd/ddocs or tools that can take an existing codemap benchmark JSON report and produce a deterministic unlabeled precision sample JSON template of 150 suggestions, and another mode to evaluate a fully labeled precision benchmark. Reuse project CLI conventions; avoid unrelated refactors.\r\n4. Generate the source suggestion report and 150-item unlabeled sample template against D:\\!bin\\space-rocks using the current tuned algorithm, under research/codemap-precision/. The sample must be deterministic and stratified across ranks, score buckets, evidence kinds, and areas. If 150 is impossible, use the largest valid size and explain.\r\n5. Do not label suggestions in this stage. Leave labels/rationales explicitly blank so a later curation pass can fill them.\r\n6. Run gofmt and focused tests, then go test ./... . Do not commit yet, because curation is still pending.\r\n7. Report the thread ID, changed files, tests, and exact generated sample path/count.\r\n\r\nPreserve unrelated dirty work. Do not modify Space Rocks. Keep hackathon logging enabled.\r\nresult= The workspace also contains a complementary `precision source` path and `SuggestCurrent` runner added by the prior work; I’m preserving and using that path because it treats authored links as visible and produces a clean current-suggestions report without holdout contamination. That run is slower than the holdout benchmark but