/player-data/playerdata/rails_store.go\\\\r\\\\n680\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n682\\\\tRails internal endpoint ownership:\\\\r\\\\n684\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n685\\\\tservices/api-server/config/routes.rb\\\\r\\\\n686\\\\tservices/api-server/app/controllers/api/internal/player_data/stats_controller.rb\\\\r\\\\n687\\\\tservices/api-server/app/controllers/internal/player_data/match_results_controller.rb\\\\r\\\\n688\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n690\\\\tRelated logical schema sources:\\\\r\\\\n692\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n693\\\\tshared/player_data/stats.toml\\\\r\\\\n694\\\\tshared/player_data/match_result.toml\\\\r\\\\n695\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n697\\\\tRelated runtime packet source:\\\\r\\\\n699\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n700\\\\tshared/packets/player_data.toml\\\\r\\\\n701\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n703\\\\t## Service responsibilities\\\\r\\\\n705\\\\t### Client\\\\r\\\\n707\\\\tThe client owns:\\\\r\\\\n709\\\\t* building hosted player-data request URLs from `ApiConfig`\\\\r\\\\n710\\\\t* sending JSON requests through `ApiHttpClient`\\\\r\\\\n711\\\\t* attaching a user bearer token when a caller supplies one\\\\r\\\\n712\\\\t* constructing profile-read request bodies\\\\r\\\\n713\\\\t* constructing local profile management request bodies\\\\r\\\\n714\\\\t* consuming profile, stats, local profile list, and default-profile responses\\\\r\\\\n715\\\\t* mapping request failures into client flow state\\\\r\\\\n717\\\\tThe client does not own:\\\\r\\\\n719\\\\t* HTTP contract source-of-truth\\\\r\\\\n720\\\\t* backing-store selection\\\\r\\\\n721\\\\t* local SQLite persistence\\\\r\\\\n722\\\\t* Rails/Postgres persistence\\\\r\\\\n723\\\\t* token verification\\\\r\\\\n724\\\\t* stat mutation authority\\\\r\\\\n725\\\\t* gameplay fact authority\\\\r\\\\n727\\\\t### Game Server\\\\r\\\\n729\\\\tThe game server owns:\\\\r\\\\n731\\\\t* hosting the player-data HTTP routes on the current HTTP mux\\\\r\\\\n732\\\\t* constructing the player-data runtime\\\\r\\\\n733\\\\t* adapting the game-server auth verifier to the player-data HTTP auth verifier interface\\\\r\\\\n734\\\\t* passing the same runtime to profile/local-profile handlers and match-result reporting\\\\r\\\\n735\\\\t* keeping hosted player-data routes separate from WebSocket and simulation behavior\\\\r\\\\n737\\\\tThe game server does not own:\\\\r\\\\n739\\\\t* player-data request behavior after delegation to handlers\\\\r\\\\n740\\\\t* local profile persistence internals\\\\r\\\\n741\\\\t* Rails authenticated-account persistence internals\\\\r\\\\n742\\\\t* OpenAPI contract ownership\\\\r\\\\n743\\\\t* client presentation\\\\r\\\\n744\\\\t* live gameplay-to-stats aggregation rules outside match-result reporting\\\\r\\\\n746\\\\t### Player Data\\\\r\\\\n748\\\\tThe player-data service owns:\\\\r\\\\n750\\\\t* profile HTTP request validation and response shaping\\\\r\\\\n751\\\\t* authenticated-account identity resolution after token verification\\\\r\\\\n752\\\\t* profile stats loading through the runtime\\\\r\\\\n753\\\\t* local profile list/create/update/delete/default behavior\\\\r\\\\n754\\\\t* local profile ID generation\\\\r\\\\n755\\\\t* local profile display-name validation\\\\r\\\\n756\\\\t* guest-stat seeding for new local profiles\\\\r\\\\n757\\\\t* mapping runtime/store errors into player-data HTTP error responses\\\\r\\\\n758\\\\t* Rails adapter request construction for authenticated-account stats reads and match-result writes\\\\r\\\\n760\\\\tThe player-data service does not own:\\\\r\\\\n762\\\\t* Rails auth token issuance\\\\r\\\\n763\\\\t* Rails/Postgres physical schema\\\\r\\\\n764\\\\t* game-server route hosting\\\\r\\\\n765\\\\t* OpenAPI contract enforcement\\\\r\\\\n766\\\\t* client UI behavior\\\\r\\\\n767\\\\t* game simulation or match outcome calculation\\\\r\\\\n769\\\\t### API Server\\\\r\\\\n771\\\\tThe API server owns:\\\\r\\\\n773\\\\t* internal token-protected authenticated-account stats reads\\\\r\\\\n774\\\\t* internal token-protected authenticated-account match-result writes\\\\r\\\\n775\\\\t* public authenticated `GET /api/player/stats`\\\\r\\\\n776\\\\t* token verification for game-server authenticated account flow\\\\r\\\\n777\\\\t* Rails/Postgres physical persistence\\\\r\\\\n778\\\\t* Rails OpenAPI contract test support\\\\r\\\\n780\\\\tThe API server does not own:\\\\r\\\\n782\\\\t* Guest persistence\\\\r\\\\n783\\\\t* Local Profile persistence\\\\r\\\\n784\\\\t* embedded SQLite storage\\\\r\\\\n785\\\\t* player-data runtime store routing\\\\r\\\\n786\\\\t* game-server-hosted player-data facade routes\\\\r\\\\n788\\\\t## Compatibility and update expectations\\\\r\\\\n790\\\\tHTTP shape changes must update:\\\\r\\\\n792\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n793\\\\tshared/contracts/http/openapi.yaml\\\\r\\\\n794\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n796\\\\tand the affected handlers, client wrappers, Rails controllers, and tests in the same change.\\\\r\\\\n798\\\\tHosted player-data profile/local-profile HTTP changes should not be made only in client scripts or only in Go handlers. The OpenAPI contract is the HTTP shape source.\\\\r\\\\n800\\\\tRuntime packet changes are separate from HTTP changes and must update:\\\\r\\\\n802\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n803\\\\tshared/packets/player_data.toml\\\\r\\\\n804\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n806\\\\tplus generated outputs.\\\\r\\\\n808\\\\tLogical player-data schema changes are separate from HTTP and packet shape changes and must update:\\\\r\\\\n810\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n811\\\\tshared/player_data/stats.toml\\\\r\\\\n812\\\\tshared/player_data/match_result.toml\\\\r\\\\n813\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n815\\\\tplus any intentionally mirrored implementation contracts.\\\\r\\\\n817\\\\tThe current implementation does not generate Godot clients, Go clients, Rails controllers, or database schema from OpenAPI.\\\\r\\\\n819\\\\t## Validation and testing\\\\r\\\\n821\\\\tHTTP contract validation:\\\\r\\\\n823\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n824\\\\tcd services/api-server && bundle exec rails test test/contracts/openapi_contract_test.rb\\\\r\\\\n825\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n827\\\\tBroader API-server validation when Rails internal player-data routes change:\\\\r\\\\n829\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n830\\\\tcd services/api-server && bundle exec rails test\\\\r\\\\n831\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n833\\\\tPlayer-data validation:\\\\r\\\\n835\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n836\\\\tcd services/player-data && go test ./...\\\\r\\\\n837\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n839\\\\tRestricted build validation:\\\\r\\\\n841\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n842\\\\tcd services/player-data && go test -tags noembeddedsqlite ./...\\\\r\\\\n843\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n845\\\\tGame-server hosted-route and composition validation:\\\\r\\\\n847\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n848\\\\tcd services/game-server && go test -buildvcs=false ./cmd/game-server\\\\r\\\\n849\\\\tcd services/game-server && go test -tags noembeddedsqlite -buildvcs=false ./cmd/game-server\\\\r\\\\n850\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n852\\\\tRelevant current tests:\\\\r\\\\n854\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n855\\\\tservices/player-data/httpapi/local_profiles_handler_test.go\\\\r\\\\n856\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/rails_store_test.go\\\\r\\\\n857\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/configured_runtime_test.go\\\\r\\\\n858\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/store_router_test.go\\\\r\\\\n859\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/noop_store_test.go\\\\r\\\\n860\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/embeddedsqlite/sqlite_store_test.go\\\\r\\\\n861\\\\tservices/api-server/test/controllers/api/internal/player_data/stats_controller_test.rb\\\\r\\\\n862\\\\tservices/api-server/test/controllers/internal/player_data/match_results_controller_test.rb\\\\r\\\\n863\\\\tservices/api-server/test/contracts/openapi_contract_test.rb\\\\r\\\\n864\\\\tclient/tests/unit/profile/test_player_data_profile_api_client.gd\\\\r\\\\n865\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n867\\\\tCovered behavior includes:\\\\r\\\\n869\\\\t* local profile routes returning `local_profiles_unavailable` when no local profile store is configured\\\\r\\\\n870\\\\t* local profile creation with zero seed stats when guest stat seeding is disabled\\\\r\\\\n871\\\\t* local profile creation copying Guest stats when guest stat seeding is enabled\\\\r\\\\n872\\\\t* Rails adapter use of `/api/internal/player-data/stats` instead of public `/api/player/stats`\\\\r\\\\n873\\\\t* Rails adapter use of internal bearer-token headers\\\\r\\\\n874\\\\t* Rails adapter match-result request shape and duplicate response handling\\\\r\\\\n875\\\\t* client profile API request body construction\\\\r\\\\n876\\\\t* client profile bearer-token forwarding\\\\r\\\\n878\\\\t## Code map\\\\r\\\\n880\\\\tHosted route installation:\\\\r\\\\n882\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n883\\\\tservices/game-server/cmd/game-server/main.go\\\\r\\\\n884\\\\tservices/game-server/cmd/game-server/player_data_http.go\\\\r\\\\n885\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n887\\\\tHosted profile and local profile handlers:\\\\r\\\\n889\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n890\\\\tservices/player-data/httpapi/profile_handler.go\\\\r\\\\n891\\\\tservices/player-data/httpapi/local_profiles_handler.go\\\\r\\\\n892\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n894\\\\tPlayer-data runtime and local profile store boundary:\\\\r\\\\n896\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n897\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/runtime.go\\\\r\\\\n898\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/store.go\\\\r\\\\n899\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/store_router.go\\\\r\\\\n900\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/configured_runtime.go\\\\r\\\\n901\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/noop_store.go\\\\r\\\\n902\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/embeddedsqlite/sqlite_store.go\\\\r\\\\n903\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n905\\\\tAuthenticated-account Rails adapter:\\\\r\\\\n907\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n908\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/rails_store.go\\\\r\\\\n909\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n911\\\\tClient consumers:\\\\r\\\\n913\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n914\\\\tclient/scripts/api/api_config.gd\\\\r\\\\n915\\\\tclient/scripts/api/api_http_client.gd\\\\r\\\\n916\\\\tclient/scripts/profile/player_data_profile_api_client.gd\\\\r\\\\n917\\\\tclient/scripts/profile/local_pilot_api_client.gd\\\\r\\\\n918\\\\tclient/scripts/ui/menu_flow/local_pilot_flow.gd\\\\r\\\\n919\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n921\\\\tAPI-server internal endpoint implementation:\\\\r\\\\n923\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n924\\\\tservices/api-server/config/routes.rb\\\\r\\\\n925\\\\tservices/api-server/app/controllers/api/internal/player_data/stats_controller.rb\\\\r\\\\n926\\\\tservices/api-server/app/controllers/internal/player_data/match_results_controller.rb\\\\r\\\\n927\\\\tservices/api-server/app/services/player_stats/apply_match_result.rb\\\\r\\\\n928\\\\tservices/api-server/app/services/player_stats/serialize_stats.rb\\\\r\\\\n929\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n931\\\\tContract and schema sources:\\\\r\\\\n933\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n934\\\\tshared/contracts/http/openapi.yaml\\\\r\\\\n935\\\\tshared/player_data/stats.toml\\\\r\\\\n936\\\\tshared/player_data/match_result.toml\\\\r\\\\n937\\\\tshared/packets/player_data.toml\\\\r\\\\n938\\\\tservices/player-data/protocol/packets.go\\\\r\\\\n939\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n941\\\\tRelated tests:\\\\r\\\\n943\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n944\\\\tservices/player-data/httpapi/local_profiles_handler_test.go\\\\r\\\\n945\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/rails_store_test.go\\\\r\\\\n946\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/configured_runtime_test.go\\\\r\\\\n947\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/store_router_test.go\\\\r\\\\n948\\\\tservices/player-data/playerdata/embeddedsqlite/sqlite_store_test.go\\\\r\\\\n949\\\\tservices/api-server/test/controllers/api/internal/player_data/stats_controller_test.rb\\\\r\\\\n950\\\\tservices/api-server/test/controllers/internal/player_data/match_results_controller_test.rb\\\\r\\\\n951\\\\tservices/api-server/test/contracts/openapi_contract_test.rb\\\\r\\\\n952\\\\tclient/tests/unit/profile/test_player_data_profile_api_client.gd\\\\r\\\\n953\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n955\\\\tImportant non-ownership boundaries:\\\\r\\\\n957\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n958\\\\tservices/game-server/internal/networking/\\\\r\\\\n959\\\\t= owns the auth verifier consumed by the HTTP adapter\\\\r\\\\n961\\\\tservices/game-server/internal/matchreporting/\\\\r\\\\n962\\\\t= owns match-result reporting into player-data\\\\r\\\\n964\\\\tservices/api-server/\\\\r\\\\n965\\\\t= owns Rails auth and authenticated-account persistence\\\\r\\\\n967\\\\tshared/contracts/http/openapi.yaml\\\\r\\\\n968\\\\t= owns HTTP request/response shapes\\\\r\\\\n970\\\\tshared/packets/player_data.toml\\\\r\\\\n971\\\\t= owns player-data runtime packet shapes\\\\r\\\\n973\\\\tshared/player_data/*.toml\\\\r\\\\n974\\\\t= owns logical player-data schema\\\\r\\\\n975\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n977\\\\t## Related docs\\\\r\\\\n979\\\\t* [Protocol](./!INDEX.md)\\\\r\\\\n980\\\\t* [API Product Surface](api-product-surface.md)\\\\r\\\\n981\\\\t* [HTTP Contract Enforcement](./http-contract-enforcement.md)\\\\r\\\\n982\\\\t* [Player Data](../services/player-data/!INDEX.md)\\\\r\\\\n983\\\\t* [Local Profiles HTTP API](../services/player-data/local-profiles-http-api.md)\\\\r\\\\n984\\\\t* [Profile Stats Flow](../services/player-data/profile-stats-flow.md)\\\\r\\\\n985\\\\t* [Runtime And Store Routing](../services/player-data/runtime-and-store-routing.md)\\\\r\\\\n986\\\\t* [Game Server Player Data HTTP Hosting](../services/game-server/integrations/player-data-http-hosting.md)\\\\r\\\\n987\\\\t* [Client HTTP API Flow](../services/client/client-http-api-flow.md)\\\\r\\\\n988\\\\t* [API Server Player Stats And Match Results](../services/api-server/player-stats-and-match-results.md)\\\\r\\\\n989\\\\t* [Player Data Schema](../data/player-data-schema.md)\\\\r\\\\n990\\\\t* [Player Data Routing Flow](../domains/platform/player-data-routing-flow.md)\\\\r\\\\n992\\\\t## Notes\\\\r\\\\n994\\\\tThe current player-data HTTP facade is hosted in the game-server process, but its behavior remains a player-data service responsibility.\\\\r\\\\n996\\\\tThe hosted HTTP profile path and generated player-data packet path are related but not identical. The HTTP profile handler validates supported play-mode and identity-kind strings, resolves identity, and calls `Runtime.LoadStats` directly. The packet dispatcher validates mode/identity combinations before store access.\\\\r\\\\n998\\\\tLocal Profile display names are presentation values. `local_profile_id` is the local durable identity.\\\\r\\\\n1000\\\\tAuthenticated Account routing uses `account_id` resolved from token verification. Rails `user_id` remains an API-server internal database identifier.\\\\r\\\\n1002\\\\tGuest stats are process-local and transient. Local Profile stats are durable only when local storage is configured. Authenticated Account stats route through the Rails adapter when Rails configuration is present.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\n===== docs/protocol/realtime-websocket-protocol.md =====\\\\r\\\\n1\\\\t## Realtime WebSocket Protocol\\\\r\\\\n3\\\\tParent index: [Protocol](./!INDEX.md)\\\\r\\\\n5\\\\t## Purpose\\\\r\\\\n7\\\\tThis document describes the current realtime WebSocket protocol between the Godot client and the Go game server.\\\\r\\\\n9\\\\tThe protocol is JSON-over-WebSocket for auth, room, lobby, signaling, and other pre-readiness/session-control packets, and JSON-over-lane-specific WebRTC DataChannels for active realtime gameplay and tooling packets: `sr.world`, `sr.overlay`, `sr.session`, `sr.event`, `sr.asteroids.lifecycle`, and `sr.bullets.lifecycle` are ordered/reliable, `sr.asteroids` and `sr.bullets` are unordered/unreliable hot-update lanes, and the mandatory `sr.tooling` lane is reliable/ordered/bidirectional with negotiated id 9.\\\\r\\\\n11\\\\tIt covers the transport route, JSON packet framing, connection lifecycle, packet-family routing, lane policy, gameplay packet families, session-state requirements, delivery semantics, source-of-truth files, generated outputs, service responsibilities, compatibility expectations, and implementation code paths.\\\\r\\\\n13\\\\t## Overview\\\\r\\\\n15\\\\tThe realtime protocol currently uses JSON text messages over a WebSocket connection for signaling and queued one-off packets, and lane-specific WebRTC physical DataChannels for active realtime gameplay packets, with ordered/reliable lanes for `sr.world`, `sr.overlay`, `sr.session`, `sr.event`, `sr.asteroids.lifecycle`, and `sr.bullets.lifecycle`, unordered/unreliable hot-update lanes for `sr.asteroids` and `sr.bullets`, and a mandatory reliable/ordered/bidirectional `sr.tooling` transport lane at negotiated id 9.\\\\r\\\\n17\\\\tThe game server exposes one realtime route:\\\\r\\\\n19\\\\t```text\\\\r\\\\n20\\\\tGET /ws\\\\r\\\\n21\\\\t```\\\\r\\\\n23\\\\tThe Godot client selects a WebSocket URL from the requested session mode, opens the connection, optionally sends an auth packet, sends room or gameplay request packets, and receives authoritative server packets. /ws is the signaling, session, and control route, not the active gameplay state transport.\\\\r\\\\n25\\\\tWebSocket owns auth, room, lobby, signaling, and queued pre-readiness/session-control packets. WebRTC physical DataChannels own active realtime gameplay packets and runtime tooling packets. Current physical gameplay DataChannels are `sr.world`, `sr.overlay`, `sr.session`, `sr.event`, `sr.asteroids`, `sr.bullets`, `sr.asteroids.lifecycle`, and `sr.bullets.lifecycle`; `sr.tooling` is the ninth required channel and already carries runtime measurement. `control` is a logical recovery category, not a current physical WebRTC gameplay DataChannel. The current generated recovery packet families are `resync_request` and `resync_required`; there is no generated packet family named `control`, and there is no physical `sr.control` channel in the current implementation. The WebSocket URL may point at the normal hosted or proxied service route, but WebRTC DataChannel connectivity is established by ICE candidates rather than by a WebRTC URL. Deployment must allow the advertised WebRTC ICE address to reach the game server directly. Cloudflare-proxied HTTP routes should not be assumed to carry WebRTC DataChannel traffic.\\\\r\\\\n27\\\\tThe route path does not define play mode. Local single-player and multiplayer currently use the same local WebSocket route during development. Single-player versus multiplayer behavior is expressed through packets, session identity, room state, admission policy, and player-data routing.\\\\r\\\\n29\\\\tThe WebSocket conn"}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f7acb-d75e-7bf1-aeb8-348db6878711"}}}
